Defendant Alexander L Leisten in court, in custody, with attorney Daniel P Fay.   Susan L. Opper and Lesli Boese appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Amended Information filed by the State.   Defendant enters a guilty plea to Count 1.  Court finds defendant guilty. 

Court orders the following: 
Ct. 1:
- Total sentence:  7 years (Initial Confinement: 3 1/2 years - 76 days credit, Extended Supervision: 3 1/2 years)
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Challenge Incarceration 
- Defendant IS NOT eligible for Substance Abuse Program. 
- Court Costs totaling $268.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision; alternate 6 days jail consecutive. 
- Restitution totaling $10,436.00 to be paid Archie B.'s family for funeral expenses as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- Restitution totaling $100.00 from file 14CF881 (dismissed and read-in) to be paid to Metro Drug Unit as a Condition of Extended Supervision.
- DNA Surcharge totaling $250.00 to be paid as a Condition of Extended Supervision; alternate 5 days jail consecutive. 
- Conditions of Extended Supervision: Defendant to pay all restitution and court costs and follow all rules of extended supervision. DNA Sample if not yet provided.
